# SCAN Development Conventions

## Project Context

This is the **Splunk Cisco App Navigator (SCAN)** — a React-based Splunk app
that serves as the front door to the Cisco–Splunk ecosystem. The main UI is a
single-page app in `index.jsx` backed by `products.conf` as the product catalog.

## Key Files

- **Main UI**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/src/main/webapp/pages/products/index.jsx`
- **Product catalog**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/src/main/resources/splunk/default/products.conf`
- **Catalog spec**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/src/main/resources/splunk/README/products.conf.spec`
- **CSS**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/src/main/resources/splunk/appserver/static/products.css`
- **Catalog generator**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/bin/generate-catalog.js`
- **Architecture Guide**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/docs/SCAN_Architecture_Guide.md`
- **Decision Log**: `packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/docs/DECISIONS.md`

## Decision Log

After completing any significant design decision or feature, add a dated entry
to `DECISIONS.md` in the package docs folder. This is the institutional memory
that survives chat sessions. Format:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Short Title
**Decision:** What was decided.
**Rationale:** Why.
```

## Visual Consistency Sweep (Mandatory)

When changing any visual element (color, badge, icon, label, filter name), you
MUST search for ALL occurrences across the entire codebase before considering
the task complete. The same element can appear in:

- **Card badges** (product card rendering)
- **Help / Guide modal** ("How to Use SCAN")
- **Filter drawer pills**
- **Category bar buttons**
- **Stats bar tiles**
- **Customer summary export** (HTML + plain text)
- **CSS classes** (light mode + dark mode overrides)
- **Inline styles** in JSX

Use grep/search for the element name, CSS class, label text, and color hex
values. A visual change is not done until every surface is updated.

## Dark Mode (Mandatory)

Every UI change MUST account for dark mode. The app uses `:root.dce-dark`.

- New CSS classes need both a light-mode rule AND a `:root.dce-dark` override.
- Use CSS custom properties (`var(--card-border, #ddd)`, `var(--page-color, #333)`)
  over hardcoded hex in inline styles where possible.
- Badge dark-mode pattern: translucent `rgba()` backgrounds, lighter text colors.
- Verify visual correctness in both themes before considering any UI task complete.

## Git Workflow

- Branch naming: `TENG-<Jira Number>` (mandatory).
- Prefer stacked/topic commits: one logical change per commit.
- Never modify git config. Never force-push to main/master.
- Always use `--no-verify` only if the user explicitly asks.

## Coding Standards

- Use `@splunk/react-ui` components and `@splunk/react-icons` for native look.
- Badge color palette: cool non-status tones (no red/yellow/green for categories).
- products.conf `sourcetypes` field: comma-separated, alphabetical order.
- `date_updated` must be set to today whenever any product field changes.
- After editing products.conf, regenerate: `node packages/splunk-cisco-app-navigator/bin/generate-catalog.js`

## Ask vs. Do

When the user asks "what do you think about X?" or "should we do X?" — that is
a QUESTION, not an instruction. Provide your opinion and wait for explicit
approval before making changes. Watch for question marks and advisory phrasing.
